      "rationale": "Residuals for momentum and continuity equations reduced to 1e-4 and held stable over the final 200 iterations; the 1e-5 target was not reached due to rotating-reference-frame instabilities at the impeller-volute interface at the highest RPM operating point (3500 RPM, 2.5 L/min). The team judged convergence adequate based on stable force and torque monitors, and the final solution was accepted without further investigation of the residual plateau. Mass imbalance of 0.08% was noted but not flagged as a concern. Time-step sensitivity was assessed only at the nominal operating point and not extended to the worst-case condition. Solver error level assessed as 1, below the required level 2 for MRL 2.",
